      | Lists
    h3
      | When to Use
    p
      | Lists are great for presenting a series of related phrases or sentences that need to be read faster.
    h3
      | Which to Use
    p
      | Foundation styles allow for a multitude of lists, including: <code>ul</code> for generic lists and <code>ol</code> for numbered lists.
    h3
      | How to Use
    p
      | Note the code snippets under each subheading on the left; look there for required classes and list markup.
    h3
      | Editing the CSS
    p
      | CSS for list styles can be found in <code>_settings.scss</code> and the variables are <code>$list-*</code>.
